          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a specific numeric format known as \"overpunch\" into a monetary value. Overpunch is a method used in mainframe systems to encode the sign of a number within the last digit of a numeric string. This function interprets such strings and converts them into a SQL Server "
